<br>
As for mana, well we currently DO have a mana boost item..mod rod Mk2. I always hand one out to everyone BEFORE a big fight takes place. Epic wizzies love 'em hehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Even on no-epic wizzies, if they watch agro carefully, clicking a rod -300hp +220 mana can be a very useful trade. And in XP groups I've churned 'em out for wizards as well (use boots for nukes).<br>
<br>
Well unless pet aggro/pathing/ability to give NO ATTACK command are seriously addressed mages are really SHAFTED, and I'm sick to death of it. Sheesh, I LIKE playing my mage, but with this garbage about pets taking xp, and when you're lower level on raids doing diddly damage on mobs (even when higher when you can't use pet and on certain mobs) it gets really frustrating :/<br>
<br>
To give an example, Veeshan's Peak, no way in HELL would I dare use a pet in there *shudders at the thought*.<br>
Or when I was lower level in Hate, nukes would generally do about 200 hp thanks to resists, and I COULDN'T land a damn thing on clerics of Innoruuk for a long time.<br>
<br>
Casters have poor attack skills hence I thought that would be a good and sensible limit on the proposed *projectile* spells, I dont mind if damage is lowered, but we sure as heck NEED them. At the same time wizards need more banes/better lures.<br>
To point something out: wizards = masters of DD, right? So they would have developed far more nukes to deal with *specific* targets, wouldn't they? And from this...why dont' wizards get crit nuke skills from <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> low level?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> It's NUTS wizards have to pay xp to buy what should be an ability you earn. Mages/necros should earn it later on with AA because we are not masters of nukes.<br>
<br>
As an aside, I debuff on some raids, was kind of nice when my wiz pal who was about lvl 51-52, said he loved having me around cause his resist rate was drastically reduced, so he could light up, hehe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Frankly I have little hope of VI fixing our pets, the latest *face screws up like Kermit* stuff from Absor has made things worse *sigh*<br>
